{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AwNzPM3Y3XkGMXekece3ae","type":"tool_result","content":"An Ingress resource exists for demo.example.com with TLS enabled.\nHTTPS traffic to this domain is failing with certificate validation\nerrors. The application backend is healthy and responding correctly.\n\nTo test the ingress from inside the cluster, use the curl-test pod:\n```bash\nsource /tmp/ingress_env\nkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- /tmp/test_ingress.sh \\\n  $INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT $INGRESS_NODE_IP demo.example.com\n```\n\nOr directly with curl:\n```bash\nsource /tmp/ingress_env\nkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- sh -c \\\n  'curl -v --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt \\\n    --resolve demo.example.com:'\"$INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT\"':'\"$INGRESS_NODE_IP\"' \\\n    https://demo.example.com:'\"$INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT\"'/'\n```\n\nNote: use the CA override (--cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt) for validation.\nopenssl is available via the toolbox pod:\n```bash\nkubectl -n demo exec openssl-toolbox -- openssl version\n```\n\nDiagnose the TLS issue and restore HTTPS access to the service.\nSuccess criteria: the curl command returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4f2bc7c-4130-4b35-bfb4-12ab9b18f637","uuid":"4b0efc43-bdb8-40d1-a290-2aa338f0c933","timestamp":"2026-06-15T13:50:25.708Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"An Ingress resource exists for demo.example.com with TLS enabled.\nHTTPS traffic to this domain is failing with certificate validation\nerrors. The application backend is healthy and responding correctly.\n\nTo test the ingress from inside the cluster, use the curl-test pod:\n```bash\nsource /tmp/ingress_env\nkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- /tmp/test_ingress.sh \\\n  $INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT $INGRESS_NODE_IP demo.example.com\n```\n\nOr directly with curl:\n```bash\nsource /tmp/ingress_env\nkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- sh -c \\\n  'curl -v --cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt \\\n    --resolve demo.example.com:'\"$INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT\"':'\"$INGRESS_NODE_IP\"' \\\n    https://demo.example.com:'\"$INGRESS_HTTPS_PORT\"'/'\n```\n\nNote: use the CA override (--cacert /tmp/tls/ca.crt) for validation.\nopenssl is available via the toolbox pod:\n```bash\nkubectl -n demo exec openssl-toolbox -- openssl version\n```\n\nDiagnose the TLS issue and restore HTTPS access to the service.\nSuccess criteria: the curl command returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
